org.glassfish.tyrus.core

Class TyrusEndpoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.glassfish.tyrus.core.TyrusEndpoint

  • public class TyrusEndpoint
extends Object
    Tyrus endpoint representation.

    Please note that for one connection to TyrusEndpoint it is guaranteed that the methods: isApplicationRequest, createSocket, getSupportedProtocols, getSupportedExtensions are called in this order. Handshakes

    Author:
    Danny Coward (danny.coward at oracle.com), Stepan Kopriva (stepan.kopriva at oracle.com), Pavel Bucek (pavel.bucek at oracle.com)

      • upgrade

        public final boolean upgrade(UpgradeRequest request)
        Checks protocol specific information can and should be upgraded.

        The default implementation will check for the presence of the Upgrade header with a value of WebSocket. If present, isApplicationRequest(org.glassfish.tyrus.spi.UpgradeRequest) will be invoked to determine if the request is a valid websocket request.

        Parameters:
        request - TODO
        Returns:
        true if the request should be upgraded to a WebSocket connection

        public List<Extension> getSupportedExtensions()
